## Avoid

- Creating a new connection per request or per function call.
- Keys without TTLs for session or cache data.
- Pickled Python objects for data that crosses deployments.
- Using Redis as a primary database for relational data.
- Catching `redis.RedisError` silently without logging or fallback.
